result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamie Paul Kampa was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manufacture/Deliver Heroin (<=3G), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(d)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: In the event that the defendant is discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent SHALL notify the court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment SHALL be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

miscConds.notes: Defendant is to pay court costs, including a blood draw fee and the DNA surcharge.  Bond money is to be applied.  Balance of bond money is to be applied to costs in Tremp. Co. Case No. 16 CF 60.
Defendant is to receive an AODA evaluation and follow through with any recommended treatment.
Defendant is not to consume alcohol or enter bars/taverns.
Defendant is to provide a DNA sample.    Defendant is to complete any treatment/programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and agent.

timeConds.notes: Defendant is to perform 40 hours of community service each year while on probation.

judgments.action: Guilty Due to No Contest Plea
